snippet: Six city workers died and 28 people were injured in a protest after a march by residents demanding better schools and more teachers.
abstract: Six city workers die of asphyxiation and 28 people are injured when protesters, demanding better schools, set fire to municipal building in El Alto, Bolivia.
lead_paragraph: Six city workers died and 28 people were injured in a protest after a march by residents demanding better schools and more teachers.

headline.print_headline: The Americas; Bolivia: Demonstrators Set Deadly Fire
